<div class="container">
    <h1 id="title">ui-code-hightlight</h1>
    <h2>Code highlighting using highlight.js</h2>
    
    <h3>code-block</h3>
    <div class="row">
        <desc>
            the <code>code-block</code> component is a block helper which allows code fragments represented in your 
            templates to be code highlighted. You may optionally provide:
            <ul>
                <li><strong>language</strong> 
                    <ul>
                        <li>you can be explicit about what language is involved</li>
                        <li>if you leave this off then it will try to auto-identify</li>
                        <li>if you're lazy you can just use <code>lang</code> as it's setup as an alias</li>
                        <li>
                            if you're stating multiple languages via an array you find it more appropriate to use  
                            <code>langs</code> or <code>languages</code> because ... guess what? ... they're setup as aliases
                            too
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>border</strong> 
                    <ul>
                        <li>a boolean flag which indicates whether a border should be painted around the code</li>
                        <li>
                            the default border color is a light grey and defined by the  
                            <code>span.ui-code-highlight.border</code> CSS selector
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </desc>
    </div>
    
    <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-5">
        handlebars:
{{#code-block language="handlebars"}}
\{{#code-block}}
foo = [ 1,2,3 ];
foo.forEach(function(item) {
    console.log(item);
});
\{{/code-block}} 
{{/code-block}}
    </div>
