    <h3>code-reference</h3>
    <div class="row">
        <desc>
            The <code>code-reference</code> component is an inline helper which allows you to point to variables 
            and have them highlighted with 
            <ul>
                <li><strong>referenceItem</strong> 
                    <ul>
                        <li>allows binding to this variable, the code view of this variables content is then displayed</li>
                        <li>you may also use the alias <code>ref</code> as a shorthand way of doing the same thing</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>border</strong> 
                    <ul>
                        <li>same as <code>code-block</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </desc>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-5">
        {{#code-block language="handlebars" border=true}}
\{{code-reference ref=snippetFunction  border=true}}
        {{/code-block}}
        
        <note>
            <strong>Note:</strong> 
            this presumes a property exists on <strong>application.js</strong> called <code>snippetFunction</code>
        </note>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-7">
            {{code-reference ref=snippetFunction  border=true}}
            <note>
                which of course it does :)
            </note>
        </div>
    </div>

